imgAlt: ['People wait outside a Department of Motor Vehicles office in Oakland on May 8. The DMV on Friday said it would further extend some expired licenses.', 'The Girl and The Fig, a Sonoma bistro, has been closed during to the pandemic. Some Sonoma restaurants are reopening with outdoor seating.', '"Human parking spots" are marked at Mission Dolores Park seen during lunch time on Thursday, May 21, 2020, in San Francisco, Calif. San Francisco Recreation & Parks Department painted social-distance guidance circles on the parks lawn.', 'U.S. Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi speaking at a Capitol Hill press conference accused Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell of obstructionism regarding the relief bill.', 'A couple sunbathe on Cowell Beach in Santa Cruz in April. Warm Memorial Day weekend weather will test the Bay Areas shelter-in-place resolve.', 'Commuters prepare to board a westbound Capitol Corridor train at the Amtrak station in Berkeley in 2018. Additional trains will be added to its schedule starting June 1.', 'People chat and embrace outside The Stud Bar in San Francisco in 2016. The 54-year old bar will close its current location at Harrison and Ninth Streets and look for a new location.', 'Redwoods at the Henry Cowell Redwood State Park in Felton is seen in 2015. California State Parks began reopening some parking lots Tuesday after they were closed to discourage crowds during shelter-in-place orders.']

title: Coronavirus LIVE: With 338 fresh Covid-19 cases, Delhi's tally crosses 6,000-mark - India Today
h1: ["Coronavirus LIVE: With 338 fresh Covid-19 cases, Delhi's tally crosses 6,000-mark"]
h2:
['03:54 AM IST: The World Health Organization (WHO) said on Friday that although a market in the Chinese city of Wuhan selling live animals likely played a significant role in the emergence of the new coronavirus, it does not recommend that such markets be shut down globally.
In a press briefing, WHO food safety and animal diseases expert Peter Ben Embarek said live animal markets are critical to providing food and livelihoods for millions of people globally and that authorities should focus on improving them rather than outlawing them -- even though they can sometimes spark epidemics in humans.', "03:52 AM IST: The number of people in Italy who've died with COVID-19 infections has topped 30,000. The Health Ministry registered 243 deaths on Friday, bringing the total of those who died in the country to 30,201. Italy was the first country in Europe with a major outbreak of the coronavirus. Authorities say many more likely died with the infection at home or in nursing homes without being diagnosed.", "03:51 AM IST: Tamil Nadu: A special flight from United Arab Emirates (UAE)'s Dubai, with around 182 Indian nationals - including 3 children, arrived at Chennai International Airport tonight. All passengers are being screened & tested. They'll be placed under quarantine, as per the guidelines.", '03:49 AM IST: ', '00:05 AM IST: Assam government has transferred the deputy commissioner of Cachar district after 10 people tested positive for Covid-19 in the district in last 48 hours. Ten people who returned from Ajmer Sharif in Rajasthan to Silchar in Cachar district have tested positive for coronavirus.', '23:52 PM IST: An order has been issued for constituting an enquiry committee by the Delhi government to look into the various aspects of major discrepancies in the reports of Dr Lal Path Labs.', "23:49 PM IST: Five Bihar Military Police personnel have tested positive for Covid-19, taking the state's total tally to 579.", '23:28 PM IST: Tripura reported 30 fresh cases of coronavirus persons on Friday, after which its total tally crossed the 100-mark. Tripura currently has 118 Covid-19 cases. The new cases include 25 persons from the 86th Battalion of BSF.', "23:00 PM IST: Indian Navy's INS Jalashwa carrying 698 Indian nationals has set sail from Male, Maldives. Among the 698 passengers, 595 are men and 103 are women.", '22:54 PM IST: Wife and three-year-old child of Delhi Police Constable Amit Kumar, who died due to coronavirus on Tuesday, have also tested positive for the virus. Both have been shifted to PGI Sonipat.', '22:49 PM IST: An Air India flight carrying 187 passengers from Sharjah will land in Lucknow on Saturday at 8 pm. Out of the 187 passengers, 31 are from Lucknow.', "22:31 PM IST: Delhi has reported 338 fresh cases of coronavirus in the last 24 hours, after which, its total tally has crossed the 6,000 mark. At present, Delhi's total coronavirus count stands at 6,318. Meanwhile, the national capital has reported two virus-linked deaths in the last 24 hours, with which, its death toll has reached 68.", '22:15 PM IST: Have asked all CAPFs to adopt innovative ways to contain the further spread of Corona virus among its ranks and ensure proper and timely health checks. Also instructed them to establish a dedicated hospital to treat the COVID-19 affected CAPF personnel. pic.twitter.com/uCO6vb4GJM Amit Shah (@AmitShah) May 8, 2020', '22:09 PM IST: The Punjab government has decided to promote all students of classes V to X under Punjab School Education system to the next class without any examination. Class X students under Punjab School Education Board will be promoted on basis of their performance in pre-Board exams.
The state govt has decided to promote all students of Classes V to X under Punjab School Education system to the next class without any examination. Class X students under Punjab School Education Board will be promoted on basis of their performance in pre-Board exams: Punjab Govt pic.twitter.com/rp1obvHK5K
 ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '22:06 PM IST: Karnataka government permits clubs, bars and restaurants to sell liquor in takeaway form at maximum retail price till May 17 to clear their existing stock, says official order.', "22:04 PM IST: With 51 new cases, Odisha's Covid-19 tally jumps to 270, say officials.", '22:00 PM IST: The Finance Ministry has allowed discounting of prolonged stay period in India for the purpose of determining residency status in view of the lockdown.', '21:52 PM IST: Gujarat can be stabilised for Coronavirus Casualty numbers only if Anandibehn Patel returns as CM Subramanian Swamy (@Swamy39) May 8, 2020', '21:18 PM IST: Rajasthan on Friday reported a total of 152 coronavirus cases, after which, its total count mounted to 3,579. Four deaths were also reported in the state today, taking its Covid-19 death toll to 103.', '21:03 PM IST: AIIMS director Dr Randeep Guleria and Dr Manish Sureja will be flying Ahmedabad by a special IAF flight, as per the instruction by Home Minister Amit Shah, to visit Civil Hospital and SVP Hospital to guide doctors on the treatment being given to the Covid-19 patients in the state.', '21:01 PM IST: The Noida administration has requested Air India to not allow the crew members, who are the residents of Noida and are involved in repatriation exercise, to come back to the district without following the Central government's guidelines. "They should remain in Delhi till the operation is going on," officials said.', '20:50 PM IST: Uttar Pradesh reported 155 fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday, after which, its total count has gone up to 3,214. The state has reported 66 coronavirus-related deaths so far, while, 137 coronavirus patients have recovered and have been discharged from hospitals in UP.', '20:46 PM IST: Maharashtra coronavirus updates:
-Total new cases in Maharashtra in last 24 hours: 1,089
-Total deaths in state in last 24 hours: 37
-Total deaths due to coronavirus in Maharashtra: 731
-Total cases in Maharashtra: 19,063
-Total cases in Mumbai alone: 12,142
-Total deaths in Mumbai alone: 462
-25 deaths in Mumbai in last 24 hours.
-New cases in Mumbai in last 24 hours: 748
-3,470 patients discharged till date after full recovery in Maharashtra.', '20:35 PM IST: Evacuated from Bangladesh, 160 Indian students reached Srinagar earlier today in an Air India flight.
"I am happy to be back in Kashmir. We are thankful to the Ministry of External Affairs for our evacuation," a student said.', '20:27 PM IST: Maharashtra Chief Minister Uddhav Thackeray said that this phase of the lockdown is crucial and whether the lockdown is extended or relaxed now depends on the people of the state and their adherence to the norms.', '20:24 PM IST: Telangana coronavirus bulletin:
-10 new cases in state today
-Total 1,132
-Discharged 727
-Death 29
-Active cases 376', '20:18 PM IST: The Kenyan Embassy in India has chartered IndiGo flights to fly around 200 of its national stranded here to Mumbai from various parts of the country so that they could be evacuated on a Kenyan Airways flight to Nairobi thereon.', "20:16 PM IST: West Bengal has reported 130 new cases of coronavirus in last two days, after which, the state's total tally has gone up to 1,678. The number of active cases in the state currently stands at 1,195, while it has reported a total of 88 deaths due to the novel virus so far.", '20:13 PM IST: During a press conference on coronavirus, Maharashtra Chief Minister Uddhav Thackeray said, "I'm slightly perturbed today because of the incident that took place near Aurangabad. Time and again we have appealed to the migrant labourers that they need not leave the state. We have made necessary arrangements for food, stay, health check-up etc. We are also in touch with other states and we have also started trains to ferry them."', '20:10 PM IST: Madhya Pradesh reported 89 fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday, after which, its tally reached 3,341. The state has reported 200 coronavirus-related deaths so far, with maximum - 86 - in Indore. Indore has reported 1,727 Covid-19 cases till date.', '20:05 PM IST: After 800 factories got clearance from the Noida administration to reopen amid lockdown, the first factory has opened now. India Today has learnt that it is a Lava mobile factory.', "20:02 PM IST: Uttarakhand has reported two fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday, which took the state's total tally to 63. Of the total cases, 45 have recovered and have been discharged from hospitals. The state has reported one coronavirus-related death so far.", "19:53 PM IST: Mumbai's Dharavi slum area on Friday reported 25 new cases of coronavirus. With this, the total cases in the slum area gone up to 808, while, 222 have been discharged.", "19:45 PM IST: Thirteen fresh cases of coronavirus have been reported from Uttar Pradesh's Ghaziabad district today, taking the total tally in the district to 133. Of these, 74 cases are currently active in the district. The number of hotspots in Ghaziabad currently stands at 19.", '19:43 PM IST: Restaurants, eateries, ice cream shops, sweet shops and juice shops in Ludhiana have been allowed to open for home deliveries from 7 am to 7 pm, district magistrate said.', '19:41 PM IST: For all final year students, the UGC has conveyed its desire to consult in June for exams in July. However, Minister @meudaysamant ji has conveyed to me if the covid situation continues, he will NOT risk the life of any single student and will push for the same decision as others
 Aaditya Thackeray (@AUThackeray) May 8, 2020', '19:20 PM IST: Home Minister Amit Shah on Friday held a review meeting with all director generals of Central Armed Police Forces. Shah appreciated the commendable work done by the CAPFs and also expressed his concern over the increasing coronavirus cases in the forces. He also discussed the measures needed to be taken for containing the further spread of coronavirus in CAPFs.', '19:13 PM IST: 12 ITBP (Indo-Tibetan Border Police) personnel have tested positive for coronavirus in the last 24 hours and all of them are from Delhi. The total number of coronavirus cases in ITBP has now increased to 88.', '19:10 PM IST: Sixty-three fresh cases of coronavirus have been reported from Udaipur in Rajasthan on Friday. Of these, 58 have been reported from a Muslim colony.', '19:03 PM IST: The first batch of 168 Indian students, stranded in Bangladesh due to the coronavirus-linked global travel restrictions, left for home on Friday on board a special Air India flight, officials said.
The evacuation flight carrying the students from here will land in Srinagar directly.
More such flights are also being readied by the authorities to facilitate other Indians as part of the Operation Vande Bharat - A homecoming, Indias massive repatriation operation to bring home its citizens stranded abroad. (PTI)', '18:53 PM IST: The Madras High Court has ordered closure of all state-run liquor shops in Tamil Nadu and has permitted only online sale of liquor. The online sale of liquor will be allowed only till May 17.
The order comes after complaints being raised over social distancing norms being flouted by costumers outside liquor shops in the state.', '18:33 PM IST: According to the lastest coronavirus bulletin by the Jammu and Kashmir administration, the union territory has reported a total of 823 Covid-19 cases so far and nine virus-related deaths. Meanwhile, of the 823 cases, 364 Covid-19 patients have recovered till now in J&K.', '18:24 PM IST: Six more coronavirus cases have been reported in Bihar, taking the total number of cases to 569, Bihar Principal Health Secretary Sanjay Kumar said.', '18:21 PM IST: All Covid-19 positive inmates of Arthur Road jail have been to a quarantine centre in Mahul near Chembur under proper police protection.', '18:17 PM IST: Tamil Nadu has reported 600 fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday, with 399 of them being from Chennai. The total count in the state has now gone up to 6,009. The state government said that the reason for such a high count of cases lately is aggressive testing.', "18:13 PM IST: Two more doctors of Delhi's Hindu Rao Hospital have tested positive for coronavirus. As on Friday, 10 healthcare workers of Hindu Rao Hospital and five of Kasturba Hospital have tested positive. Contact tracing is underway.", "18:10 PM IST: Nine fresh cases have been reported from Haryana's Gurugram, taking the total tally in the city to 126. Of the total cases, 75 are currently active. Meanwhile, with 74 cases being reported in eight days, Gurugram's Cyber City area has now become a red zone.", '18:02 PM IST: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh held a telephonic conversation with his Japanese counterpart Taro Kono on Friday, focusing on bilateral military cooperation as well as on ways to deal with the coronavirus pandemic. The two ministers agreed that India-Japan special strategic and global partnership provides a good basis for both countries to work together along with other countries to deal with challenges in the post-Covid-19 phase, officials said.
"Both ministers also conveyed their commitment to take forward the initiatives of bilateral security cooperation," an official said.', '18:01 PM IST: Maharashtra Minister Uday Samant on Friday said only final year students of graduate and post-graduate courses will appear for final semester examinations this year while the first and second-year students will be promoted to the next class.
The Higher and Technical Education Minister was quoted in an official statement as saying that the examination will be held between July 1 and July 30.', '17:46 PM IST: After receiving no response from the Bihar government on their share of fare to ferry the migrant workers, the Delhi government, according to sources, has decided to bear the travel expense of the Bihar migrants who will go back to their hometowns by trains.', '17:40 PM IST: Delhi High Court will hear a PIL seeking ban on the sale of liquor on May 11.', '17:39 PM IST: Government of Inida and the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB) have signed a $500 million project to fight Covid-19. The Covid-19 Emergency Response and Health Systems Preparedness Project will help in responding to the pandemic and strengthen its public health preparedness.', '17:31 PM IST: US President Donald Trump has decided that he will be tested daily for the coronavirus after one of his valets tested positive for the deadly disease.
A military aide of Trump, whom the White House officials described as a personal valet, tested positive for coronavirus.
The valet, a member of the military, would have had very close contact with Trump, and assisted him with his food, clothes and other personal needs, CBS News reported. (PTI)', '17:19 PM IST: Union Minister for Human Resource Development Ramesh Pokhriyal has announced that the pending CBSE board exams for class 10th and 12th will be conducted between July 1 and July 15. A detailed schedule will be provided by the HRD ministry shortly.
#CBSE 10 12 , 1.07.2020 15.07.2020 @HRDMinistry @PIB_India @DDNewslive pic.twitter.com/NVexiKgVA1
 Dr Ramesh Pokhriyal Nishank (@DrRPNishank) May 8, 2020', '17:17 PM IST: As of 5 pm of May 8, Karnataka has reported a total of 753 Covid-19 positive cases, including 30 deaths and 376 discharges. The state has reported 48 fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday.', '17:09 PM IST: Kerala has reported one fresh case of coronavirus today, after two days of not reporting any new case. The new case is a patient in Eranakulam who had returned from Chennai. Meanwhile, the state has reported 10 recoveries today.', '17:07 PM IST: A revised list of red, orange and green zones will be circulated to the states soon after the analysis of data, the health ministry said.', '16:57 PM IST: Two Delhi Police personnel posted at Jama Masjid Police Station have tested positive for coronavirus.', '16:56 PM IST: Noida police busted a racket of bus owners who were duping stranded migrant workers by on the pretext of ferrying them back to their hometowns. Two people have been arrested in connection with the case and both are bus drivers, while the owner of these buses is absconding.', "16:40 PM IST: Uttar Pradesh's Gautam Buddh Nagar district has reported 12 fresh cases of coronavirus on Friday, after which, its total count has gone up to 214", '16:30 PM IST: The health ministry on Friday during the routine coronavirus briefing said that there are 216 districts in India that have not reported any cases till date.
Meanwhile:
-42 districts have not reported fresh cases in last 28 days.
-29 districts have not reported fresh cases in last 21 days
-36 districts have not reported fresh cases in last 14 days
-46 districts have not reported fresh cases in last 7 days', '16:12 PM IST: The health ministry, during the routine government briefing on coronavirus on Friday, said that a total of 16,540 Covid-19 patients have recovered in India, including the 1,273 cured in the last 24 hours. The health ministry said that 37,916 patients in India are under active medical supervision currently.
In the last 24 hours, there were 3390 new COVID19 positive cases and 1273 recoveries. The recovery percentage is now 29.36%. Till now, 16,540 patients have been cured and 37,916 patients are under active medical supervision: Lav Agrawal, Jt Secy, Health Ministry pic.twitter.com/Qp0ZVUEzAN ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '16:11 PM IST: The health ministry said that India has reported 3,390 new cases of coronavirus in the last 24 hours. Meanwhile, 1,273 coronavirus patients have recovered in the last 24 hours.', "15:56 PM IST: A 60-year-old man died due to coronavirus in western Uttar Pradesh's Gautam Buddh Nagar on Friday, becoming the first fatality in the district due to Covid-19. The victim was a resident of Noida's Sector 22.
He was admitted to a private hospital in Noida earlier this week and found positive for Covid-19 on Thursday after which he was taken to the Government Institute of Medical Science (GIMS) in Greater Noida.", "15:49 PM IST: Afghan officials say the country's health minister has tested positive for the new coronavirus as the country recorded 215 new infection cases in the last 24 hours.
The ministry confirmed Friday that Ferozuddin Feroz has tested positive for the virus.
Afghanistan has recorded more than 100 deaths from the virus out of more than 3,700 confirmed cases. (AP)", '15:42 PM IST: Thirty new coronavirus cases have been reported in the Border Security Force (BSF), out of which six have been reported from Delhi and 24 from Tripura. All of them are under treatment at AIIMS Jhajjar and G B Pant Hospital in Agartala.', "15:38 PM IST: RWA organisation URJA has opposed Delhi government's decision to convert Karol Bagh hotels into paid quarantine centers for those who are being evacuated from foreign countries. They have demanded that such centers should be in non-residential areas.", '15:37 PM IST: Uttarakhand has not reported any new coronavirus case since the last three days. The state has reported a total of 61 Covid-19 cases so far, out of which 45 have recovered.', '15:22 PM IST: Around 150 Indian nationals were screened at King Khalid International Airport in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. Flight to take off for Kozhikode in Kerala to bring back the stranded Indians back home.
Around 150 Indian nationals being screened at King Khalid International Airport in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. Flight to take off for Kozhikode in Kerala, shortly. #VandeBharatMission pic.twitter.com/nipwvJq3gi
 ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '15:00 PM IST: All university students in Maharashtra, except those in the final year, will be promoted to the next class without examination due to coronavirus lockdown. The final year examinations will be held in July: State Higher and Technical Education Minister Uday Samant', '14:59 PM IST: Singapore on Friday reported 768 new cases of coronavirus, mostly among the foreign nationals living in dormitories, taking the total number of infections in the country to 21,707 with 20 deaths, the health ministry said.', '14:41 PM IST: Union Health Minister Harsh Vardhan says, "We have around 821 dedicated coronavirus hospitals with more than 1.5 lakh beds with isolation and ICU facilities in the country. Till today, we have conducted 14.40 lakh test across India. We are now conducting 95,000 coronavirus tests every day." He also added, "Today we have 453 labs with 332 govt labs and 121 private labs to test coronavirus."', '14:39 PM IST: Union Health Minister Harsh Vardhan, Minister of State for Health Ashwini Kumar Choubey holds a meeting with Health Ministers of Tamil Nadu, Telangana and Karnataka through video conference.', '14:27 PM IST: Drug Controller General of India has given approval for clinical trials of Favipiravir which is used in influenza in Japan, China etc and could be potentially useful against coronavirus alongwith phytopharmaceutical, which is an extract of a plant, says CSIR Director General Shekhar Mande.', '14:15 PM IST: The first batch of 168 Indian students, stranded in Bangladesh due to the coronavirus-linked global travel restrictions, has reached India on an Air India flight. Earlier, 234 Indians returned from Singapore on a similar flight.', '13:59 PM IST: An Air India repatriation flight from Singapore landed at the Delhi airport on Friday morning with 234 passengers, senior officials of the airline said. The flight was part of the Vande Bharat mission which started on Thursday to bring back stranded Indian nationals home amid the novel coronavirus-induced lockdown.', '13:16 PM IST: The Supreme Court has refused to pass orders to ban liquor sale. The Supreme Court has said states should consider online sale or home delivery. The Supreme Court will not interfere, it has to be a policy decision, says the court.', '12:56 PM IST: CISF has said test reports of a CISF Assistant Sub-inspector posted in Indian Museum, Kolkata who died yesterday has confirmed that he was coronavirus positive.', '12:53 PM IST: Air India flight bringing back Indians from Singapore has landed in Delhi. This is the repatriation mission of Vande Bharat to bring back Indians stranded abroad
Air Indias first flight that took off from Singapore has landed in Delhi, under #VandeBharatMission. pic.twitter.com/k4cV8ggYOC
 ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '12:51 PM IST: Indians who were stranded in Maldives, board INS Jalashwa, to return home. They are being repatriated as part of the Samudra Setu Mission.
Male: The first batch of Indian nationals who will be brought back from the Maldives under operation #SamudraSetu, board INS Jalashwa. pic.twitter.com/8lpisFbt1H
 ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '12:20 PM IST: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi on Friday said the Government must start giving transparency to its actions in fighting COVID-19 by cooperating with states and making them partners in decision-making.', '12:02 PM IST: "We have to protect job creators, build a wall for them to protect jobs, wages and we have to give them financial support. We need to start our domestic economy soon, the more time we lose, the worse impact it will have," says Rahul Gandhi.', '11:58 AM IST: "This is not the time to criticise, we need a strategy to open the lockdown. Any businessman will tell you that there is a clash between economic supply chain and 'red, orange and green zones', that need to be resolved," says Rahul Gandhi', '11:55 AM IST: Rahul Gandhi says, "We must tell people the reality. This disease is fatal for only 1% of the population not the rest of the healthy population of India. We must remove fear among the population orelese the lockdown will never be removed."', '11:50 AM IST: Rahul Gandhi says, "Only 1% of Indians are at the highest risk of coronavirus but 99% of the people are not at risk. First thing the govt must do is to remove fear of the virus from the minds of the people. Only then will opening the lockdown help. Even if you open up everything, fear will make people stay at home."', '11:41 AM IST: Rahul Gandhi says, "Our chief ministers are complaining that coronavirus zones are being decided by the Centre. This should be done by local governments."', '11:34 AM IST: Rahul Gandhi says, "The Centre must immediately transfer Rs 65,000 crore into the bank accounts of poor and migrant population to give them financial support in these difficult times. There has to be a conversation between states and Centre to oversee this."', '11:30 AM IST: Rahul Gandhi says, "The Govt needs to have transparency with its actions before it starts to open the lockdown. This lockdown in not switching on and off a key. We have to make a psychological change in the mindset of people. Opening up is a transition and the Govt needs to have a strategy to do it. It will require coordination between state govts and Centre and local administration. Asked about his well-being, Rahul Gandhi says, "I am not doing good, but okay."', '10:48 AM IST: INS Jalashwa will be evacuating Indians from Maldives.  ANI (@ANI) May 8, 2020', '10:34 AM IST: In a single day TASMACs stores in Tamil Nadu have sold liquor worth around Rs 170 crore. In a normal situation, the 5,146 TASMAC shops in Tamil Nadu sell about Rs 80 crore worth of liquor. With the lockdown 3,750 shops were opened and the collection has crossed Rs 170 crore in a day.', '10:31 AM IST: India is now evacuation stranded nationals from Maldives. The Indian nationals are about to board the INS Jalashwa from Male. The High Commission of India in Maldives has said the Indian nationals registered for repatriation will be charged 600 Maldivian Rufiyaa or an equivalent amount of US $40 as the evacuation service charge for repatriation from Maldives by INS Jalashwa under Operation Samudra Setu.', "09:23 AM IST: India has reported 3,390 new coronavirus cases and 103 deaths in 24 hours. The total number of coronavirus cases in India now stand at 56,342 while the number of active cases stand at 37,916. Total cured or discharged cases now stand at 16,539. India's coronavirus death toll has gone up to 1,886.", "08:38 AM IST: North Korea says leader Kim Jong Un sent a personal message to Chinese President Xi Jinping praising what he described as China's success in getting its coronavirus epidemic under control. China is North Korea's most significant ally and economic lifeline, accounting for about 90% of the country's external trade. With China's COVID-19 caseload easing, some experts say the North could reach out to China to reinvigorate cross-border trade that had been significantly reduced in past months.", '08:17 AM IST: The United Nations called on governments, companies and billionaires on Thursday to contribute to a $6.7 billion fund for immediate needs in fighting the coronavirus pandemic in vulnerable countries, warning that a failure to help could lead to a "hunger pandemic", famine, riots and more conflict.', '08:15 AM IST: The spread of the deadly coronavirus across the globe from China was either a terrible mistake on the part of the Chinese or probably it was incompetence, US President Donald Trump said on Thursday.', '07:58 AM IST: US records 2,448 coronavirus deaths in 24 hours, bringing the total toll to 75,543, according to Johns Hopkins University.', '07:57 AM IST: Top Republican senators has urged US President Donald Trump to suspend all new guest worker visas for 60 days and certain categories of new guest worker visas, including H-1B, for at least a year or until unemployment figures return to normal levels. The unemployment figures in the US have reached an all-time high due to the coronavirus pandemic. The letter has been signed by Senators Ted Cruz, Tom Cotton, Chuck Grassley and Josh Hawley. H-1B visa is the most popular choice among Indians working in the US and most companies hire Indian workers with this visa.', '07:53 AM IST: India on Thursday launched its biggest ever repatriation exercise and brought back 363 Indians stranded in the UAE due to the coronavirus lockdown. India sent two Air India Express flights to bring back the Indians as part of the ambitious Vande Bharat Mission. The two flights landed at Kochi and Kozhikode on Thursday. While the first Air India Express flight carrying 177 passengers and four infants from Abu Dhabi landed at Kochi at 10.09 pm, the second flight from Dubai carrying same number of passengers and five infants landed at Kozhikode few minutes later at 10.32 pm. The evacuated citizens were sent to the Institutional Quarantine facilities set up by the district administrations in their respective districts. Pregnant women, people needing immediate treatment, those returning to attend ceremonies connected to death of a close relative, aged people needing continuous assistance and children under 10 years will be permitted to go to their houses, where they will be under strict home quarantine (self-isolation) for 14 days. All passengers were asked to download Arogya Setu app on their mobile devices and submit forms of undertaking, as directed by Government of India, on their arrival at the airport, they said. The Kerala State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) buses were kept ready for transporting the evacuated expatriates.', ' Coronavirus in India Live Updates: India has launched its biggest repatriation mission to bring back Indians stranded abroad due to the coronavirus lockdown. Today, an Air India flight has brought back Indians from Singapore while the INS Jalashwa is bringing back Indian nationals from Maldives. In the first two flights of the Vande Bharat Mission, 363 Indians, who were stranded in UAE, were brought back on Air India flights that landed in Kerala. Meanwhile, the coronavirus count in India has crossed 56,000 while the death toll has crossed 1,800. Over the past few days, coronavirus cases have seen a major rise by over 3,000 cases being reported every day. United States, which is the worst-affected country, has recorded over 75,000 deaths with 2,448 people dying in the past 24 hours. Follow live updates on coronavirus:']
